  "doc_id": "19980",
  "text": "Application Programming Interface (API) is a bridge for BIM system software developers to integrate the third-party applications (plug-ins) into existing related software [CITATION_1] , which affects the information exchange and program development of the entire BIM system. APIT is mainly applied in three aspects, i.e. information transmission, program connection and program development. Information transmission means that the information inside software is extracted by API and transmitted to the place where it is needed. Program connection means that API connect the relevant software exists in BIM system with a third-party application program (plug-in) in where the certain calculation is processed. Program development refers to that the developed third-party application program (plug-in) must be API based.",
  "correct_citation": {
